Police today (November 29) appealed to the public for information on a woman who went missing in Western District.




 Law Bik-wah, aged 81, went missing after she left an elderly home on Des Voeux Road West yesterday afternoon (November 28). Staff of the elderly home made a report to Police on the same day.




 She is about 1.52 metres tall, 59 kilograms in weight and of medium build. She has a round face with yellow complexion and short greyish white hair. She was last seen wearing a grey long-sleeved shirt, black vest, black trousers, black shoes and carrying a crutch.




