Police are investigating a fatal traffic accident in Pat Heung in the small hours today (November 8) in which a 32-year-old man died.At about 4am, a private car driven by a 25-year-old man was travelling along Tsing Long Highway towards Yuen Long. After passing Tai Lam Tunnel Toll Plaza, the private car reportedly rammed into the rear part of a maintenance truck which had stopped on the second lane and the 32-year-old man who had alighted from the truck.The 32-year-old man was certified dead at scene.The private car driver was arrested for drink driving and dangerous driving causing death. He is being detained for further enquiries.Investigation by the Special Investigation Team of Traffic, New Territories North is underway.Anyone who witnessed the accident or has any information to offer is urged to contact the investigating officers on 3661 3800.
Police today (November 7) reclassified a wounding case in Castle Peak yesterday (November 6) as attempted murder.




 About 8.44am that day, Police received a report that a man was attacked by another man with a knife on Wu Chui Road. Police officers sped to the scene and found a 57-year-old man who sustained chest injury. The man was sent to Tuen Mun Hospital for medical treatment in conscious state.




 Police arrested a 30-year-old man at scene that day. He was holding charged with one count of attempted murder. The case will be mentioned at Fanling Magistrates’ Courts tomorrow afternoon (November 8).




 Active investigation by the Regional Crime Unit of New Territories North is underway.


A man who went missing in Mong Kok has been located.




 Ng Siu-tong, aged 76, went missing after he was last seen on Ka Shin Street on November 5 afternoon. His family made a report to Police on the same day.  




 The man was located on Lai King Hill Road today (November 7) noon. He sustained no injuries and no suspicious circumstances were detected.


A man who went missing in Hung Hom has been located. Li Jiawen, aged 49, went missing after he left a hostel on Lok Shan Road on October 23 afternoon. His family made a report to Police on October 31. The man was located at a hospital in Cheung Sha Wan yesterday afternoon (November 6).
