 Radical protestors today (September 29) continue to gather in Admiralty and Wan Chai, charging police cordon lines. Some of them even hurled numerous petrol bombs at police officers, posing a serious threat to the safety of everyone at scene.




 In face of the situation, police officers are using appropriate force to disperse radical protestors in Admiralty and Wan Chai, and will soon embark on a dispersal operation in Causeway Bay.




 Police warn the radical protestors to stop all illegal acts and leave immediately. Due to the chaotic situation, members of public are advised to avoid travelling to the area.
Attention duty announcers, radio and TV stations:




Please broadcast the following message as soon as possible and repeat it at suitable intervals:




 Radical protestors today (September 29) have blocked carriageways and committed destructive acts extensively in Admiralty and Wan Chai. The protestors confronted police at Admiralty Road and Hennessey Road. Some radical protestors vandalised facilities at Wan Chai MTR Station and hurled petrol bombs at Police officers. Another group of protestors started fires at Admiralty Road near Admiralty MTR Station, posing a serious threat to the safety of everyone at scene.




 After repeated warnings to the radical protestors went futile, police officers have deployed tear gas in multiple locations in Admiralty and Wan Chai in view of the situation, using appropriate force to disperse radical protestors.




 Police appeal to everyone at scene to leave immediately. Members of the public are advised to avoid travelling to the areas concerned. Police condemn all violent acts by the radical protestors.
Attention duty announcers, radio and TV stations:




 Please broadcast the following message as soon as possible and repeat it at suitable intervals:




 The report room services of Wan Chai Police Station are suspended temporarily.




 Police appeal to members of the public not to obstruct the emergency vehicles access so as to avoid affecting the emergency services provided to the public. In case of emergency, please dial 999.
Attention duty announcers, radio and TV stations:Please broadcast the following message as soon as possible and repeat it at suitable intervals:A large group of protestors today (September 29) has gathered at the junction of Hennessy Road and Yee Wo Street, Causeway Bay, blocking carriageways.In view of the situation, police officers have deployed tear gas, using appropriate force to disperse protestors.Police appeal to everyone at scene to leave immediately.Residents of the area are advised to stay tuned to the latest situation and if necessary, keep their windows shut and stay indoors.
Attention duty announcers, radio and TV stations:




 Please broadcast the following message as soon as possible and repeat it at suitable intervals:




 A large group of violent protestors are gathering outside Central Government Offices. They are hurling hard objects to vandalise the glass panels outside Central Government Offices. Some protestors also set up barricade at Harcourt Road.




 Police reiterate that appropriate force is being used to disperse protestors. Police appeal to everyone at scene to stop their illegal acts and leave immediately.




 The report room services of Wan Chai Police Station are now temporarily suspended. In case of emergency, please call 999.
Attention duty announcers, radio and TV stations:




 Please broadcast the following message as soon as possible and repeat it at suitable intervals:




 Radical protestors threw petrol bombs at Central Government Offices, posing a serious threat to the safety of everyone, including police officers at scene. Police deploy appropriate force to disperse the protestors. Police warn protestors to stop any illegal acts and leave immediately. 




 Police also remind members of the public in the vicinity to stay tuned to the latest situation and stay indoors.
Attention duty announcers, radio and TV stations:




 Please broadcast the following message as soon as possible and repeat it at suitable intervals:




 A large group of violent protestors are occupying Harcourt Road, Admiralty. They also hurled bricks at Police officers. Their acts pose a serious threat to the safety of everyone at scene.




 Police will soon use appropriate force to conduct a dispersal operation. Police appeal to everyone at scene to stop their illegal acts and leave immediately.
A boy who went missing in Chai Wan has been located.




 Chang Miu-sum, aged 13, went missing after he left his residence in Siu Sai Wan Estate in mid-September. His family made a report to Police on September 22.




 The boy was located in Siu Sai Wan Estate this afternoon (September 28). He sustained no injuries and no suspicious circumstances were detected.
Attention duty announcers, radio and TV stations:




 Please broadcast the following message as soon as possible and repeat it at suitable intervals:




 At around 7.30pm, a large group of protestors are blocking the carriageways in Harcourt Road, seriously paralysing the traffic. Some violent protestors have damaged properties outside Central Government Complex and aimed laser beams at a helicopter, posing a serious threat to the safety of everyone at scene.




 Police warn the protestors to stop all illegal acts at once. Police appeal to members of the public to avoid travelling to the area and stay tuned to the latest traffic arrangement.
Attention duty announcers, radio and TV stations:




Please broadcast the following message as soon as possible and repeat it at suitable intervals:




At around 6.30pm, some protestors charged Police cordon line and pointed laser beams at police officers at the entrance of Central Government Complex.




Having given repeated warnings to the protestors but in vain, Police have used minimum force.




Police warn the protestors to stop their illegal acts immediately.
Police will implement the following special traffic arrangements in various districts to facilitate grave-sweepers, and to ensure smooth vehicular traffic movements and pedestrian safety during Chung Yeung Festival.




 Chai Wan



 --------




 Roads in the vicinity of the cemeteries in Chai Wan will be closed in phases on September 28 and 29, October 1, 5, 6, 7, 12, 13, 19, 20, 26 and 27, and November 3 and 10.




 Phase I




 Vehicles will be allowed to use Cape Collinson Road east of Lin Shing Road (vehicles can turn left from Lin Shing Road to Cape Collinson Road leading to the vicinity of Chinese Permanent Cemetery) between 8am and 6pm daily on September 28, October 1, 5, 12, 19, 26 and 27, and November 3 and 10. Depending on the traffic conditions, Phase 2 road closure may be implemented.




 Phase II




 The following roads will be closed between 8am and 6.30pm daily on September 29, and October 6, 13 and 20:




 1. The slip road leading from Cape Collinson Road to the Garden of Remembrance and Crematorium, except for hearses and funeral vehicles;



 2. The slip road leading to Chai Wan Chinese Permanent Cemetery;



 3. Cape Collinson Road east of Lin Shing Road, except for green minibus(GMB) route 18M, hearses, funeral vehicles, and vehicles with permit;



 4. Cape Collinson Road west of Lin Shing Road, except for franchised buses, GMB routes 16A, 16M and 16X, hearses, funeral vehicles and vehicles with permit;



 5. Southbound Lin Shing Road, except for franchised buses, GMB routes 16A, 16M, 16X and 18M, hearses, funeral vehicles, vehicles with permit and vehicles to Wan Tsui Estate and Lin Tsui Estate; and



 6. Northbound Lin Shing Road, except for GMB route 18M, hearses, funeral vehicles and vehicles with permit.




 Depending on traffic conditions, taxis and public light buses (PLBs) may be allowed to enter southbound Lin Shing Road and turn right to Cape Collinson Road. Traffic along Lin Shing Road cannot turn left to Cape Collinson Road.




 Phase III




 The following roads will be closed between 8am and 7pm on October 7:




 1. The slip road leading from Cape Collinson Road to the Garden of Remembrance and Crematorium, except for hearses and funeral vehicles;



 2. The slip road leading to Chai Wan Chinese Permanent Cemetery;



 3. Wan Tsui Lane;



 4. Cape Collinson Road east of Lin Shing Road, except for hearses, funeral vehicles and vehicles with permit;



 5. Cape Collinson Road west of Lin Shing Road, except for franchised buses, GMB routes 16A, 16M and 16X, hearses, funeral vehicles and vehicles with permit; and



 6. Lin Shing Road, except for franchised buses, GMB routes 16A, 16M and 16X, hearses, funeral vehicles, vehicles with permit and vehicles to Wan Tsui Estate and Lin Tsui Estate.




 In connection with the road closure as mentioned above, the following roads will be re-routed one way westbound:




 1. Cape Collinson Road between the slip road to Crematorium and Shek O Road; and



 2. The eastern section of Wan Tsui Road between Chai Wan Road and Fei Tsui Road.




 No parking will be permitted along Cape Collinson Road, Lin Shing Road, Shek O Road between Tai Tam Gap Correctional Institution and Tai Tam Road, and Wan Tsui Road.




 In connection with the road closure as mentioned above, all taxis, PLBs and private cars heading for Cape Collinson Road cannot enter Lin Shing Road, except making access to Wan Tsui Estate and Lin Tsui Estate. Affected vehicles will be allowed to set down passengers at the public light bus stand at Fei Tsui Road near its junction with Wan Tsui Road.




 PLBs cannot pick up/set down passengers along Wan Tsui Road between Chai Wan Road and Lin Shing Road.




 Pok Fu Lam



 ----------




 Consort Rise between Victoria Road and Bisney Road will be re-routed one-way southbound from 7am to 5pm daily on October 5, 6 and 7.




 Aberdeen



 --------




 The following roads will be closed from 7.30am to 5.30pm daily on September 29, and October 1, 5, 6, 7, 12, 13, 19 and 20:




 1. Peel Rise in the vicinity of the Aberdeen Chinese Permanent Cemetery; and



 2. The slip road from Shek Pai Wan Road leading to the Aberdeen Chinese Permanent Cemetery.




 Central



 -------




 Tramway Lane between Garden Road and the office of World Wide Fund for Nature Hong Kong will be closed from 8am to 8pm on October 7, except for taxis and franchised buses. Affected vehicles will be diverted to the unnamed road between Garden Road and Cotton Tree Drive near Champion Tower.




 All metered parking spaces on Tramway Lane, motorcycle parking spaces and disabled parking spaces will be suspended between 6am and 8pm on October 7.




 The Peak



 --------




 The following traffic arrangements will be implemented between 8am and 8pm on October 7:




 1. Northbound Peak Road outside Peak Galleria will be closed, except for residents’ vehicles and vehicles with permit. Affected vehicles will be diverted to southbound Peak Road via the slip road next to the entrance of Peak Galleria car park;



 2. Lugard Road, Harlech Road and Mount Austin Road will be closed, except for residents’ vehicles and vehicles with permit;



 3. Traffic control will be implemented at the entrance of Peak Galleria car park. The vehicular access to Mount Austin Road is restricted for local residents only;



 4. All metered parking spaces and motorcycle parking spaces on Mount Austin Road near Victoria Peak Garden will be suspended; and



 5. If necessary, westbound Mount Austin Road between its junction with Peak Road and the entrance of Mount Austin Playground will be closed. As such, eastbound Mount Austin Road will be re-routed as one-lane two-way.




 Diamond Hill



 ------------

 Road closure




 The following roads will be closed between 7am and 6pm daily on September 28 and 29, and October 1, 5, 6, 7, 12, 13, 19 and 20, except for hearses and funeral vehicles:

 1. The access road leading to the Diamond Hill Crematorium;



 2. The access road between the Diamond Hill Funeral Parlour and the China Light and Power (CLP) Sub-station; and



 3. The access road adjacent to the Diamond Hill Funeral Parlour leading to Sze Chen Hall.




 The following roads will be closed between 7am and 6pm daily on September 28 and 29, and October 1, 5, 6, 7, 12, 13, 19 and 20, except for private cars and taxis:




 1. Yuk Hok Lane; and



 2. Yuk Wah Street east of Tsz Wan Shan Road.




 Motorcycles will be allowed to use Yuk Hok Lane and Yuk Wah Street east of Tsz Wan Shan Road on September 28 and 29, and October 1, 19 and 20.




 Traffic diversions




 The following traffic diversions will be implemented between 7am and 6pm daily on September 28 and 29, and October 1, 5, 6, 7, 12, 13, 19 and 20:




 1. Vehicles can only enter or leave Fung Shing Street or Fu Shan Estate car park via southbound Po Kong Village Road downhill;



 2. Vehicles can only enter or leave Grand View Garden car park via northbound Po Kong Village Road uphill;



 3. Vehicles can turn left from eastbound Po Kong Village Road to westbound Yuk Wah Street via easternmost traffic lane of Tsz Wan Shan South Bus Terminus;



 4. Traffic along westbound Fung Shing Street cannot turn right to northbound Po Kong Village Road uphill;



 5. Traffic along northbound Po Kong Village Road uphill cannot turn right to eastbound Fung Shing Street;



 6. Traffic along Grand View Garden car park cannot turn right to southbound Po Kong Village Road downhill;



 7. Traffic along southbound Po Kong Village Road downhill cannot turn right to Grand View Garden car park;



 8. Traffic along Fu Shan Estate car park cannot turn right to northbound Po Kong Village Road uphill;



 9. Traffic along northbound Po Kong Village Road uphill cannot turn right to Fu Shan Estate car park;



 10. Traffic along southbound Po Kong Village Road downhill cannot turn right to Po Kong Village Road School Village car park;



 11. Traffic leaving Po Kong Village Road School Village car park cannot turn right to southbound Po Kong Village Road downhill;



 12. Traffic along southbound Po Kong Village Road downhill cannot turn right to the unnamed road opposite to Po Leung Lane;



 13. Traffic along the unnamed road opposite to Po Leung Lane cannot turn right to southbound Po Kong Village Road downhill;



 14. Vehicles leaving Tsz Wan Shan South Bus Terminus cannot turn right to eastbound Yuk Wah Street, except for franchised buses; and



 15. Traffic along Yuk Wah Crescent cannot turn right to eastbound Yuk Wah Street.




 Suspension of parking spaces




 The following parking spaces will be suspended between 7am and 6pm daily on September 28 and 29, and October 1, 5, 6, 7, 12, 13, 19 and 20:




 1. Metered parking spaces on the unnamed road between the Diamond Hill Funeral Parlour and CLP Sub-station; and



 2. Five metered parking spaces in Yuk Wah Street car park.




 Motorcycle parking spaces in Yuk Wah Street near Yuk Hok Lane will be suspended between 7am and 6pm daily on October 5, 6, 7, 12 and 13.




 Po Kong Village Road School Village car park will be closed between 7am and 6pm on October 6, 7 and 13, except for private cars and taxis.




 Cheung Sha Wan



 ---------------




 Road closure




 1. The unnamed road leading from Wing Ming Street to the cemetery will be closed between 7am and 7pm daily on September 28 and 29, and October 5, 6 and 7; 



 2. Wing Ming Street will be closed between 7am and 7pm daily on October 5, 6 and 7; and



 3. Entrance road to the cemetery on Wing Tak Road will be closed between 7am and 5pm daily on October 5, 6 and 7, except for hearses, funeral vehicles and vehicles with permit.




 No stopping or parking




 The following traffic arrangements will be implemented on October 5, 6 and 7:




 1. Parking will be prohibited on Yu Chau West Street between Castle Peak Road and King Lam Street between 7am and 7pm daily;



 2. Vehicles are prohibited to drop off or pick up passengers along Yu Chau West Street near Wing Ming Street; and



 3. Stopping or parking will be prohibited on Ching Cheung Road between 7am and 7pm daily.




 Suspension of on-street parking spaces




 All parking spaces on Yu Chau West Street; Tai Nan West Street; and King Lam Street and Wing Hong Street between Yu Chau West Street and Tai Nan West Street will be suspended between 7am and 7pm daily on October 5, 6 and 7. 




 Members of the public wishing to gain access to the catholic cemetery are advised to use the subway across Ching Cheung Road from the end of the unnamed road leading from Wing Ming Street to the cemetery. No parking facilities in the cemetery will be open to public use.




 Tseung Kwan O



 -------------




 The access road leading to Tseung Kwan O Chinese Permanent Cemetery will be closed from 5.30am to 6pm daily on September 29, and October 5, 6, 12, 13, 20 and 27, except for special bus service by Kowloon Motor Bus (KMB) route 14S, hearses, funeral vehicles and vehicles with permit.




 The above road will be closed to all vehicular traffic from 5.30am to 8pm on October 7.




 Grave-sweepers can reach the cemetery on foot via the access road on Ko Chiu Road or the footpath with staircases opposite to MTR Tiu Keng Leng Station. Wheelchair users are advised to enter the cemetery via the access road on Ko Chiu Road.




 Sai Kung



 --------




 A section of Mang Kung Wo Road leading to Kei Pik Shan Cemetery in Sai Kung will be closed from 8am to 5pm daily on October 5, 6, 7, 12 and 13, except for vehicles with permit.




