 At around 4.30pm today (September 15), radical protestors set fire at multiple locations in Central and Admiralty, some of them also blocked exits and damaged facilities of MTR Admiralty station. Carriageways in Harcourt Road near Central Government Offices are occupied, causing serious obstruction to the traffic.




 Police will shortly disperse the protestors. Police warn the protestors to stop their illegal acts and leave the scene immediately. Members of the public are advised to avoid travelling to Central and Admiralty.


