Police today (September 14) laid a holding charge against a 56-year-old man with one count of murder.




The man was arrested yesterday (September 13) in connection with a murder case happened in Castle Peak in which his 42-year-old girlfriend died.




The case will be mentioned at Kowloon City Magistrates’ Courts today.
Police today (September 13) appealed to the public for information on a man who went missing in Kwai Chung.




 Yan Hon-ming, aged 71, went missing after he left his residence on Wo Tong Tsui Street on September 11 morning. His family made a report to Police yesterday (September 12) afternoon.




 He is about 1.6 metres tall, 64 kilograms in weight and of medium build. He has a long face with yellow complexion and short white hair. He was last seen wearing an apricot long-sleeved shirt, apricot long trousers and carrying a hiking stick and brown backpack.




 Anyone who knows the whereabouts of the missing man or may have seen him is urged to contact the Regional Missing Person Unit of New Territories South on 3661 1176 or 6317 7858 or email to rmpu-nts-2@police.gov.hk, or contact any police station.

Yan Hon-ming, aged 71, is about 1.6 metres tall, 64 kilograms in weight and of medium build. He  has a long face with yellow complexion and short white hair. He was  last seen wearing an apricot long-sleeved shirt, apricot long trousers  and carrying a hiking stick and brown backpack.
Police today (September 13) reclassified a body found case in Castle Peak on September 10 as murder.




 About 11.15am on September 10, Police received a report from a 45-year-old woman that her younger sister collapsed in a unit in Ting Tak House, On Ting Estate.




 Police officers sped to the scene and found the 42-year-old woman lying unconsciously on bed. Sustaining injuries to her neck, the woman was certified dead at scene. Officers later found the woman’s 56-year-old boyfriend lying inside the unit. The man was sent to Tuen Mun Hospital in unconscious state and later regained consciousness.




 Upon investigation, Police believed that the deceased was attacked by the 56-year-old man and her nose and mouth had been covered by plastic tape. The 56-year-old man was arrested for murder this afternoon and is being detained for further enquiries.




 Post-mortem examinations on the deceased cannot ascertain the cause of her death. Further toxicological examinations will be arranged.




 Active investigation by the District Crime Squad of Tuen Mun is underway.
A man who went missing in Wong Tai Sin has been located.




 Wong Cheuk-man, aged 81, went missing after he left his residence in Wang Tau Hom Estate yesterday morning (September 12). His family made a report to Police on the same day.




 The man was located in a hospital in Cheung Sha Wan this afternoon (September 13). No suspicious circumstances were detected.
Police today (September 13) announced that the Anti-violence Hotline service (the Hotline) has been suspended.Police launched the Hotline on September 10 in order to assist in the prevention and detection of crime by receiving anti-violence intelligence including photos, recordings and videos through WhatsApp from members of the public.Since the Hotline started to operate, a large amount of information was received and at the same time, there were different opinions on the Hotline.  As a result, Police decided to suspend the Hotline. Police will continue to explore various channels to collect information for the prevention and detection of crime.
